          "title": "THROUGHOUT THE RICH WORLD, THE YOUNG ARE FALLING OUT OF LOVE WITH CARS",
          "summary": "The car was a defining technology of the 20th century, but its appeal is waning in the 21st century, particularly among young adults. Reasons for this include the growth of the internet, the rise of taxi apps, increasing insurance premiums for young drivers, a lack of secure employment and home ownership, longer periods of education, and the threat of climate change. This shift is creating support for cities around the world to implement anti-car policies.",
